div.p: Iterate through 4KB bitmap buffer (uint8_t[4096]). Scan byte-by-byte to skip fully-used regions (0xFF) using word-aligned loads where possible.
Identify the first '0' bit within the target byte 0xFE (Binary: 11111110). Ordering: Little-Endian (LSB is index 0).
Map the bitmap index to the physical disk block offset. LBA = Region_Start + Index
Update bitmap on disk via Read-Modify-Write.
